summary: No one can stop me from headcanoning cute Danbeau shit as much as I want so I headcanon that Carol can sing (because Brie has a...
body: No one can stop me from headcanoning cute Danbeau shit as much as I want so I headcanon that Carol can sing (because Brie has a beautiful voice OBVIOUSLY) and not just in a karaoke way… like in a stop and listen in hushed awe kind of way. But she doesn’t do it much except for the fun drunken nights at Pancho’s, and even then it’s just half-assed. Actually singing is kind of a soft personal thing for her and one night little Monica has been having trouble sleeping and Maria has tried EVERYTHING and she’s so damn tired. So Carol offers to stay later and tells her that she will take over. She rocks Monica and talks to her before finally settling on singing to her. Something like “Isn’t She Lovely” by Stevie Wonder. Monica settles down and starts to listen and drift off, and Maria had just come back to check on them because moms worry y'know but she stops to watch/listen without interrupting. And that’s the moment she realizes she loves Carol Danvers.
